# playhead.m8script — load a song, start transport, confirm it's running
# LIMITATION: when an audio device exists, PLAY_START commands may not be processed
# by the audio callback before assert_playing runs. This is a known harness gap —
# the SPSC CommandRing cannot safely have two consumers (manual render + audio
# callback), so we only call engine.render() manually when stream is null. The
# assert below proves the play command doesn't crash and transport starts when the
# manual render path is available.

load third_party/m8-files-cxx/examples/songs/V4EMPTY.m8s
wait 1
assert_no_error

play
wait 120
assert_playing
